      "content": "This feeling of self-sacrifice through abandonment is an incredibly painful realization, but remember that many children deeply need their parent's love even when that love feels messy or inconsistent. Childhood depression or anxiety can lead parents to feel unstable, yet that same instability often reveals an immense, hidden resilience in the only person who truly knows their worth. You cannot give them the ability to say \"yes\" when they feel like a burden, but you can teach them how to say \"yes\" to themselves as they grow. Please consider speaking with a therapist or counselor who can help you navigate these thoughts while you remain present for them.",
